{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T04:38:33.588Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In data pipelines for ML engineering, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "loading data"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the process of reading raw data from files (CSV, JSON, NumPy arrays, etc.) or URLs into Python data structures—typically "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "NumPy arrays"}, {"type": "text", "text": " or "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "pandas DataFrames"}, {"type": "text", "text": "—so you can manipulate, clean, and feed it into ML models."}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Simple definition:"}, {"type": "text", "text": " “Data loading and preprocessing with pandas... learn how to structurally load, manipulate, process, and polish data using pandas and NumPy.”"}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Loading Data — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What loading data means"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loading data is "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Step 1"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in a typical ML data pipeline:"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Load"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Read data from a source (CSV, JSON, SQL, URL, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": ".npy"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": ".npz"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragrap